  "text": "Environmental stress impairs the activity of the thylakoid membrane by disruption of the membrane, thereby, inhibiting the activities of membrane-associated electron carriers and enzymes and resulting in reduction of the PSI and PSII and photosynthesis rate [CITATION_1] . Fluctuation of light intensity affects the architecture and protein distribution of thylakoids. It has been shown that chloroplasts in the shade havea higher density of thylakoids per chloroplast sectional area and more extensive grana stacks, and thereby more granal thylakoids than chloroplasts in the sun [CITATION_2] indicating variation in the capacity of photosynthetic electron transport.",
